news.title: Adani family looks to sell 4.5% in Ambuja Cements to raise funds
news.para: These entities are looking to raise a little over Rs 3,000 crore through the proposed secondary sale. Equity amounting to 4.5% of the company may be sold by way of block deals, the people cited said.

news.title: NGT rejects PNB's plea for de-sealing of residential property used for commercial activity
news.para: ​The tribunal was hearing the bank's petition, according to which the PNB had earlier sanctioned a loan of Rs 250 crore to a person by creating an equitable mortgage of the property in Chanakya Place here, and for the realisation of the dues, it had auctioned the collateral property to another person.

news.title: CPM state secretary assures houses for 3.4 lakh landless people in Kerala
news.para: The government will find 15,000 acres for these landless. For the 1.5 lakh people who have land but no houses, the government would provide houses through various welfare schemes.

news.title: Seven entities in race to acquire Asian Hotels (West)
news.para: The listed Asian Hotels (West), which operates Hotel Hyatt Regency near Mumbai airport, was admitted for corporate insolvency proceeding last September.

news.title: Cabinet approves Odisha apartment bill 2023
news.para: The cabinet gave its nod to the apartment bill to make the laws governing housing projects comply with the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016, a senior government official said.

news.title: Residents evacuated from Dombivali housing complex to get rent from builder, says local MP
news.para: He met Kalyan Dombivali Municipal Corporation chief Bhausaheb Dangde and others on Wednesday on the issue. The housing complex is situated in Nilje village on the Shilphata road.

news.title: Over 11,200 tillers in Punjab to get ownership rights over land as President gives assent to bill
news.para: ​The Punjab Bhondedar, Butemar, Dohlidar, Insar Miadi, Mukarraridar, Mundhimar, Panahi Qadeem, Saunjidar, or Taraddadkar (Vesting of Proprietary Rights) Bill, 2020 was passed by the Punjab Assembly in 2020 when the Congress government led by Amarinder Singh was in power.

news.title: No warning now, buildings without plan approval to be bulldozed: Ludhiana civic body chief
news.para: Aggarwal said if the owner has chosen to get himself involved in illegal constructions by not getting the building plan approved as per the norms, then the officials can demolish the building at foundation levels without issuing any warning to the owner.

news.title: Kaisa Group's long-delayed results reveal big losses
news.para: Kaisa is one of several of Chinese developers that have defaulted on their offshore debt in the past year amid a cash squeeze and slowing sales, with some now scrambling to enter into restructuring agreements with their creditors.

news.title: Indore administration cancels registration of two land deals
news.para: According to cooperative department’s deputy commissioner Madan Gajbhiye, former office-bearers of ‘Devi Ahilya Shramik Kamgar Sahkari Sanstha Maryadit’ had allegedly sold its total 1.89 acres of land, which was meant to develop plots and allot it among its members, to a Gurgaon-based private company.

news.title: China: Kaisa Group's shares plunge as trade resumes after year-long halt
news.para: Those results, released late on Thursday, showed a 12.7 billion yuan ($1.8 billion) net loss for 2021 as well as a 7.7 billion yuan loss for the first half of last year.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government rolls out m-sand policy; BIS certification must
news.para: Nearly 80% of builders use M-sand as it's cheaper than river sand. The government has promised to cancel licences if rules are not followed.

news.title: Finance ministry tightens definition of beneficial owners under PMLA
news.para: Under the anti-money laundering law, 'reporting entities' are banks and financial institutions, firms engaged in real estate and jewellery sectors. They also include intermediaries in casinos and crypto or virtual digital assets.

news.title: Cidco's Rs 699 crore spend on consultants questioned
news.para: Cidco has awarded the contract collectively worth over Rs 699 crore to provide marketing, branding, sales and post-sales services for its 67,000 residential and commercial units developed under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojna (PMAY) project.

news.title: Maharashtra budget: Housing scheme named after PM; 10 lakh units planned
news.para: Fadnavis reiterated the government's commitment to the Prime Minister's Housing for All, 2022, scheme announcing a programme for construction of 10 lakh houses in rural areas.
